                <h2 data-uuid="a98264f8d7c34291904fbd6b048e4419"> Essential Question–Writing</h2>
                <p class="white" data-uuid="ee65770c5a1c4321b9ab91702e3bd810">In this module you’ve learned about the debates
                    that swirled around the creation and ratification of the Constitution. You’ve
                    also learned about the features of the government created under the
                    Constitution and the rights and responsibilities of U.S. citizens. Now it’s
                    your turn to demonstrate your understanding of the module content by writing an
                    essay.</p>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="dcaadb110d4544b4a7f483b9755a93ed">Which ideas in the Constitution are most
                important for preserving freedom?</h3>
            <p data-uuid="f29c3e8d593f4b76becf829af21e3e9f">Write a persuasive
                essay answering this question. Your essay should specify where in the
                Constitution these ideas are expressed and provide relevant background
                information. Be sure to cite evidence to support your
                position, and organize your essay into an introduction, body, and conclusion.</p>
        </section>
